The Vice President expresses gratitude for the work being done in Vietnam by USAID. She believes that we are entering a new era that is defined by the interconnection and interdependence of people. She emphasizes the importance of collaboration and empowering leaders across sectors to address challenges and empower all people. The Vice President acknowledges the progress made in Vietnam, such as reducing poverty and advancing transgender rights, but notes that there is still more work to be done. She highlights the need for full accessibility for people with disabilities, equal access to healthcare for transgender individuals, and the eradication of gender-based violence. The Vice President emphasizes that society is stronger when everyone can participate and pledges the support of the United States, particularly through USAID, for advocacy and leadership in Vietnam.